<text>Growing-point running averages

The growing-point running averages are a sequence of cummulative sums, averaged by the number of addends, of a given sequence. For example, the growing-point runnings averages of the sequence {a, b, c, d}, are {a, (a+b)/2, (a+b+c)/3, (a+b+c+d)/4}.

Growing-point running averages can be used to show the tendency of convergence as the data points increase.

See also simple running average and exponential running averages.

   
